The Nigerian Meteorological Agency (NiMet) has predicted thick dust haze condition over the North down to the Central region for Sunday. NiMet’s weather outlook on Saturday in Abuja further predicted moderate dust haze with horizontal visibility range of 1to 3KM and localised visibility to less than or equal to 1000M for Southern parts of the country. “For Northern states, thick dust haze condition is anticipated over the Northern part of the country within forecast period with day and night temperatures of 20 to 28 degree Celsius and 6 to 13 degree Celsius. “For Central states, thick dust haze condition is anticipated over the Central part of the country with day and night temperatures of 22 to 33 degree Celsius and 8 to 18 degree Celsius,” it said. According to NiMet, moderate dust haze condition is expected over the Southern states with horizontal visibility range of 1to 3KM and localised visibility to less than or equal to 1000M. “Day and night temperatures of the region are expected to be 29 to 36 degree Celsius and 11 to 22 degree Celsius respectively,” it said.